Preconditions:
The tasks array must not be null.
The tasks array must not be empty.
The value of n must be a non-negative integer.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the least number of units of time required to finish all the given tasks.
The CPU should finish all the tasks in the given tasks array.
The CPU should follow the specified cooling period of n units of time between two same tasks.